D.q[6899] = "Really? I won\'t be able to delay the trial forever, Judge Satirev Onivin is an impatient man and making him wait too long could go against Kit Dingaround.\nI\'ll go talk to him. You go back to Ture Inge and urge him to speed up the examination.";
D.q[464] = "Good molning, my lold, and may I say how wondelful it is to see a fliendly face on this island. Oul countly is infested by tellible cleatules, whose accent is so thick and speech so slulled that we have difficulty undelstanding the slightest wold they say. \nThey came up out of the soil and attacked duling the night. Oh, it was tellible, and thele was nothing we could do! \nI can see in youl eyes full of love and compassion that you have come to save us. \n \nPlease take cale my lold, oul island is a little stlange. It is impossible to set up shop hele, and telepoltation is folbidden. To entel the acculsed Wa Wabbit\'s castle, you must have in youl possession the special keys that you\'ll find in the alea infested by those damn labbits. But do not be aflaid, my lold, fol the gleat spilit of the fox is with you.";
D.q[1712] = "Disciple, you still have many things to learn, what do you want to know ?";
D.q[6079] = "";
D.q[2307] = "Attshoo! Kuf! Snirfl... *Really unhealthy Tofu breath*";
D.q[1734] = "Disciple, you still have many things to learn, what do you want to know ?";
D.q[5108] = "";
D.q[1448] = "BUT I ASKED YOU TO LOSE! You\'re about to find out what happens when I\'m angry!";
D.q[1738] = "Disciple, you still have many things to learn, what do you want to know ?";
D.q[1737] = "Disciple, you still have many things to learn, what do you want to know ?";
D.q[7403] = "";
D.q[6080] = "";
D.q[2291] = "Beeeeeek?";
D.q[5468] = "But you see what makes this story funny is the unseemliness of the situation which brings a bear, plantigrade without the ability to speak, to order a beer in a tavern... unless, of course, it\'s the fact that you\'re not even surprised by this setting of the story...";
D.q[6900] = "Roy Sigfred won\'t be long. Don\'t worry, I\'ll do my best to get Gnirreh\'s confession in record time. Go and rest before the trial, judging by the look on your face you need it. Amayiro will let you know once the trial begins.";
D.q[137] = "You can\'t play, you don\'t have enough Kamas to wager that much. Try with a smaller amount or come back with more Kamas.";
D.q[469] = "Thewe, on youw belt, are those the keys of my two bwothews? They must have fought hawd, defending theiw life until the vewy end. You must be a tewwible wawwiow. Hewe, take my key, wesistance is futile...";
D.q[3050] = "Check this out! Rookie\'s on duty!\nLet\'s rebel! Yaahaa!";
D.q[3734] = "Ah yes! The Celestial Militia. The twelve gods appointed them to guide innocent young souls through their first days of adventure. They\'re like a brotherhood, created to teach the basics to inexperienced adventurers like you. Their symbol is a sword on a shield. I used to have pennants emblazoned with the symbol hung up on the wall here behind me, but some nefarious mouth breather stole them. To be honest though, I only hung them there to keep the wind out! It gets so chilly round here, you see.";
D.q[1666] = "Yep! Ever since he left that old cave of his he\'s spent all his time in his plush new dungeon.";
D.q[4717] = "Do you have the iron? It seems to bring bad luck upon whoever wears it... well, it is cursed afterall. Well, I don\'t really care to be honest, it\'s the demonic properties I\'m interested in!";
D.q[3535] = "Congrats! You managed to get rid of them!\nHurry up and jump in the waggon! All we need to do now is follow the tracks.";
D.q[6901] = "Judge Satirev Onivin is difficult to convince, especially since he hates business dragging.";
D.q[2495] = "Greetings, stranger! Now listen carefully, I won\'t say this twice: On the orders of Grandapan, every single adventurer who sets so much as a toe on Pandala island has to pay the McSheth levy.";
D.q[240] = "Who are you? Get lost! Ohhh... I see! You\'re trying to steal my treasure! But it\'s mine. Got it? Mine, I tell you! Anyway, I won\'t tell you where it is! Not a word! Nothing!";
D.q[7404] = "";
D.q[3417] = "Very few adventurers know the real name of this rat. All we know is that he was the pet of a Pandawushu Master named Hamatawan Yoshawa who used to live in an exotic archipelago close to Pandala Island. Endowed with extraordinary abilities for his species, this rat could learn his master\'s art only through mime while observing him train in his dojo.\nBut Yoshawa had an enemy within his dojo, the famous Pandawushu Master known as Orukawa Nagitan.";
D.q[2693] = "Indeed, you look a lot stronger! I can share my worries with you. Some of us have been very nervous since new arrivals set foot on our ancestral island. Not all Pandawas obey the laws of Grandapan! Pandikazes, those rebels, are the worst! Incidentally, the seller who unloaded this hat on you might be one of them... And this mysterious illness infecting the Enutrofs of Astrub is not helping... Be careful... Every day, more Enutrofs come... I\'m up to my eyes in work! See for yourself, go talk to Pyrite...";
D.q[6902] = "Unfortunately it\'s too late, Judge Satirev Onivin is waiting for us and for the trial to begin. We\'ll have to make do without Gnirreh\'s confession, so I\'m counting on you to prove him guilty and clear Kit Dingaround.\nThe court is adjacent to the room where Ture Inge and Satirev Onivin work, we\'d better hurry.";
D.q[3783] = "Do you wish to return to your statue, young one?";
D.q[3785] = "Do you wish to return to your statue, young one?";
D.q[3784] = "Do you wish to return to your statue, young one?";
D.q[6903] = "Kit Dingaround\'s trial is about to begin. We\'re waiting in court, which is adjacent to the room where Ture Inge and Satirev Onivin work.";
D.q[5485] = "Ah? And according to you which flower is the most beautiful of all?";
D.q[3449] = "Now I\'ve got the ingredients, I\'ll prepare the recipe. Wait there.";
D.q[3126] = "But... you\'ll have to find... the old Rigoulak... by yourself... All I know... is that he used to hide... in a primitive... cemetery...\nHe always... wanted to... be like me... as calm... and quiet... \nHe\'ll... probably... be very happy... to meet you... if you bring him... my set...\nWhich item... do you want?";
D.q[6789] = "What are you talking about? The only hair you\'ve got in your palms is yours!";
D.q[4427] = "More spies? I\'d have been surprised that Kaffra hasn\'t attacked Bonta before now if I didn\'t see what he\'s up to. He must be afraid that Justfa Lafs sent under-equipped militiamen intentionally so as to encourage us to rush headlong into battle. Unfortunately for him, we\'re a lot smarter than he thinks. We have to find weaknesses in the Bontarian militia before we attack.";
D.q[2525] = "A drink, a drink, a driiiinnk, that\'s what I need WooHoo. What do you want? I\'m praying. And when I\'m praying, I get thiiiirsty... ";
D.q[6495] = "Don\'t be expecting me to thank you for your generosity. I\'m a Rogue. When they were teaching manners at school, I took the day off. Get it?";
D.q[8024] = "";
D.q[4756] = "Merlanmagus sent you? Well in that case, I\'ll tell you what you need to do. I\'ve prepared things for you, all you need to find are some farmers, alchemists, a little potion and the spell. \nThe farmers stand on the white marks... and make sure they\'re able to grow oats, or they may ruin everything. The alchemists stand on the black marks and they must be able to use Freyesque Orchids in their potions. If you\'re an alchemist or a farmer yourself, you can stand on either the black or white mark. If not, just let me know when everyone\'s in their place.";
D.q[3879] = "Ah, very good! You found a way to return! Congratulations! Okay, now, go and find Vil. Whatever you do, please don\'t start a fight with him! I only want to talk!";
D.q[8025] = "";
D.q[4146] = "Thanks to you, I\'ll be able to breed all the creatures I need for several days.";
D.q[6095] = "";
D.q[5849] = "Don\'t blush so, cutie! To be honest, I didn\'t notice anything out of the ordinary, but maybe you should go question that dirty tell tale, Rocco. And how about you bring me back a present from your little trip. That would make me so happy!";
D.q[3866] = "Do you know how the rogues helped the demon As\'Ruoy\'Dnim to escape?";
D.q[8026] = "";
D.q[4740] = "With these new things you\'ve brought to me, we\'ll have to step our investigation up a notch, but Judge Satirev Onivin may not share that opinion - he hates lengthy investigations. We must get more time for our enquiries.";
D.q[7405] = "";
D.q[5850] = "Don\'t blush so, cutie! To be honest, I didn\'t notice anything out of the ordinary, but maybe you should go question that dirty tell tale, Rocco. Maybe you could come back afterwards and we could hang out?! I know a really nice place where the hottest guys in the region are just there for the taking... so are you in?";
D.q[6790] = "";
D.q[1606] = "This powder can heal any pet. Give it to your the creature as if it was its ordinary food and it\'ll feel better before you can say \'tiny vomiting animal\'. Just remember that this stuff is medicine and it can\'t be used to feed you r pet.\nSo, are you interested?";
D.q[2810] = "You\'re not ready. Come back later...";
D.q[4260] = "With this staff, I\'ll be able to carve a particularly efficient scythe shaft. The only thing left to do is to take the blade of your sword apart...\nAnd here you go! Your weapon\'s ready. But be careful and don\'t go reaping wheat with it, you might set fire to the field.";
D.q[6102] = "";
D.q[8027] = "";
D.q[2669] = "Don\'t judge a book by its cover. If you challenge me you\'ll soon find out I\'m a fierce opponent!";
D.q[3989] = "Don\'t distwact me! We\'ve othew things to do.";
D.q[6101] = "";
D.q[3928] = "Strange things happening at the castle? Not really. We just had a visit from Allisteria. Usually, she never leaves her Gobballs alone.";
D.q[356] = "They\'re Scrolls of Agility my grandmother left me. God rest her soul. I exchange them for 70 acorns. I love acorns. I really wonder why...";
D.q[6104] = "Shhh... not so loud, the report on the Assembly is secret, remember.";
D.q[1492] = "Are you going to tell me everything?";
D.q[1637] = "Don\'t waste your time with people like this. If they insist send an eagle or a message to the guard of Amakna. But don\'t play their game, it will only make things worse for you...";
D.q[4036] = "We\'re facing a disaster. Obviously, the parents of the groom are Wabbits. And obviously, their guests are cawwot eaters. But we don\'t have cawwots here. Can you get me some?";
D.q[8028] = "";
D.q[7667] = "";
D.q[1089] = "You\'re on leave! Haven\'t I told you?\n";
D.q[8029] = "";
D.q[4059] = "My potions are so efficient that they\'ll make you forget your spells like no other potion could ever do. Once you drink my potion, the spell that you forget will go back to its lower level of power!\nThen, you\'ll be able to learn other spells more quickly to change your fighting technique.";
D.q[2530] = "Mmhh... It\'s a great honour for us Pandawas to venerate our goddess! Your eyes are shining like a star and it\'s a sign that never lies. I know I can trust you... Go do your libations and come back!";
D.q[3736] = "My speciality is encouraging gobby young louts like you to leave my inn!";
D.q[1695] = "Choose your prize.";
D.q[1720] = "Choose your prize.";
D.q[3389] = "What? Who sent you? Who? No, no, no, I don\'t have time for this! Niiiiiiiiiiiiihhhh the Master? The Master! Take the key and get out! Get out! Off my sight! Rahhhh! The key, the keys!";
D.q[6506] = "Don\'t worry, we\'ve caught Xephires. Here, take him to Amayiro yourself, it\'s thanks to you that we found out about his treason after all. Just try not to let him get away this time.";
D.q[7406] = "";
D.q[8030] = "";
D.q[2112] = "Don\'t you speak Iop? That\'s a shame...";
D.q[1559] = "Moo oom thonks om lot moo oom!";
D.q[5434] = "";
D.q[3365] = "Check this out! A little acorn that already believes it\'s an oak! How are you planning to prove your valour? Nothing short of a miracle...";
D.q[3390] = "What?! How dare you come back without having finished your mission? No! Get out! The Master won\'t be happy! No, no, no.... He\'ll be furious! Get out! I don\'t know you. Go finish what you must finish! Just go now!";
D.q[1400] = "Doon\'tt diisturrb meee. I\'mm stuudyiiing seensiiitiiive fiiiileees.";
D.q[8031] = "";
D.q[3429] = "E=MC²... I dreamt this last night! What can it mean?";
D.q[2071] = "Hey, have a look at that, a solid link to nature, as master Sadida wouId say. And I think it\'s going to prove pretty useful : nature felt something foreboding in the galleries, and several Enutrofs are in jeopardy! If you have time before your nap, you can go and check what\'s going on. I\'ve to assist our master in his very demanding task...";
D.q[7407] = "";
D.q[8032] = "";
D.q[2670] = "You\'re welcome. May the goddess protect you touri....adventurer! ";
D.q[84] = "You\'re a real brute!";
D.q[1022] = "Nice! It\'s as sharp as ever. The smith did an outstanding job!";
D.q[7408] = "";
D.q[8033] = "";
D.q[4664] = "Aftew youw visit, I decided it was time fow me to take my wevenge on Eltuwt. I\'m a loyal wawwiow, and if you like, we could attack Eltuwt togethew. Just stawt the fight and I\'ll come to youw aid.";
D.q[7409] = "";
D.q[5757] = "";
D.q[6879] = "Look, if you\'re intending to steal my adorable Bow Meow, I\'ll gut you and make black pudding out of your entrails. You can\'t say I didn\'t warn you.";
D.q[7410] = "";
D.q[6115] = "";
D.q[7108] = "Of course, if you have enough Doploons, I\'ve plenty of little trinkets to trade.";
D.q[4519] = "Hello, Nara told me through his friend Norb that he needed some basic materials to make a prototype of his new set for the militia. You must go see Norb, get everything Nara needs and bring it back to him. That shouldn\'t take too long and you can go relax at the Bagrutte Inn when you\'re done.";
D.q[6116] = "Greetings... you seem tired. How did the Assembly of Protectors go?";
D.q[8034] = "";
D.q[7082] = "";
D.q[7411] = "";
D.q[3627] = "Egg for Piwi. Goblins like for eat egg. Only food easy for steal for them.";
D.q[5276] = "";
D.q[4362] = "Ecaflips? Let me think... no, not in the last few days.";
D.q[1662] = "Take some time to buy a souvenir from the fair. It will remind you of your the marvellous time you spent here during those long winter evenings. You can always come back, we are open the whole year round.";
D.q[6002] = "";
D.q[8035] = "";
D.q[6041] = "Ehh... hello, what can I do for you?";
D.q[7083] = "";
D.q[8036] = "";
D.q[6881] = "I used to play with dolls a lot, but since I met this little Bow Meow, my life has changed. It\'s as if I had a kind of enlightenment. Since that day, I spend all my time cuddling him. Sometimes he plays with my hair. It\'s a bit painful but it makes so happy. Other times, he falls asleep on my tummy, his head nestled on my chest. He looks so calm and serene it would be cruel to wake him up or move him.";
D.q[4563] = "What did I ever do to Djaul to be surrounded by a bunch of dullards like these? I told the militiaman to go just ahead of me, not three bloody kilometres away.";
D.q[4686] = "Ah, there you are. I have some important things to tell you.";
D.q[8037] = "";
D.q[2284] = "Hi there! What can I do for you?";
D.q[5275] = "";
D.q[6882] = "Hi, you\'re probably wondering what a renowned hunter and fisherman like me is doing here. Well, I\'ve decided to retire. I now use my talents in looking after the Bow Meow you see there, lolling on his cushions. I hunt the food he needs, and Xela is responsible for making edible. I also catch fish for him to play with and he has them for dessert. He loves raw fish, and he\'s allowed to play with his food before eating it. You should see how easily he guts fish with a single swipe of his paw.\nA word of advice: do not think about kicking him up the arse or I\'ll be forced to reduce you to ashes or turn you into pâté for him to eat.";
D.q[197] = "Enter the labyrinth? You must be joking, I can hear your knees knocking together from here! Ha ha! Come back again when you have more experience.";
D.q[6590] = "Nobody could imagine what torment this Bwork Mage has been through, but until now, no Bwork Mage has ever dared to recreate the Grafioze curse, since they knew that Sadida would punish them even more harshly. Believe me, they\'re quite right to be afraid.";
D.q[6250] = "That\'s not what I\'m asking you, you little brat. Another comment like that and I\'ll stretch your tongue so long you\'ll be able taste farther that you can see.";
D.q[591] = "Not another one! \"Enjoy the calm of a desert island!\" they said. \"Savour a glass of rum in a quiet place far away from pillages and battles!\" they said. Pfft, what with the noisy local rabble, I\'ve now got tourists coming by thinking my boat is an attraction! I must fix that hole, everybody thinks it\'s a door!";
D.q[6834] = "Hello, was Robin Gaywould more cooperative? I don\'t want to resort to violence to get information from him, we are not Brakmarians, after all.";
D.q[8038] = "";
D.q[5775] = "Do you want me to go along with you to Allister\'s castle?";
D.q[7075] = "";
D.q[823] = "We have a mole posted within the ranks of the Bonta Militia, his name is Finche Aticus.\nI asked him to make plans of Bonta\'s defence systems. Find him and bring me his report.";
D.q[1604] = "To equip an item, take it out of your inventory and wear it.\nThis way you can benefit from its magical effects.";
D.q[1274] = "All right, all right #1, you\'re stronger than me...";
D.q[3304] = "Pnj(802) et Message(3302)";
D.q[8039] = "";
D.q[5576] = "Even if the words that come out of your mouth are as horrid as your breath, I\'ll listen to you.";
D.q[1348] = "*Scissors*\nHem, I lost. You\'re not too bad... Let\'s play the second round.";
D.q[1990] = "Thanks again.\n*Yol makes Locette drink the potion, she cringes at the stench and pungency of it, she opens her eyes and coughs*";
D.q[3249] = "Quite obviously you\'ll need a key to enter the sanctuary. The only way for you to get one is to ask a skilled Handyman to make you one. To make it, you\'ll need to find shell pieces that only the four Dreggon guards have. I don\'t know where you can find these Dreggon guards but we sometimes see them coming out of abandoned houses at night. If I were you, I\'d go explore the different homes of this village.";
D.q[8040] = "";
D.q[839] = "You finally managed to capture that Bontarian! But...what about the documents? Where are the documents?\nOh... you forgot about them?! A guard told me the Bontarian lost them as he was running away. Go and get them back. Go through the moors with a fine-toothed comb if you must, but I want those documents, understood?";
D.q[846] = "Mak Gahan dealt with the last larvae. No worries. As a reward, I promised him you\'d find him dentures with gold teeth instead of Gobball teeth. Where are you supposed to find such a thing? Not my problem.";
D.q[8041] = "";
D.q[7668] = "You are already an alchemist.";
D.q[5585] = "Well a one-legged turtle would have been faster than you but you\'re lucky that the other militiamen aren\'t back either. Well the only thing I can think of to annoy all the others is to appoint you to the rank of Knife Fighter. But don\'t be fooled your skills have nothing to do with it!";
D.q[3351] = "But you need a key to get into this dungeon! I can sell you one.";
D.q[8042] = "";
D.q[7669] = "You\'re either already training for a profession or you\'ve learnt enough professions already.";
D.q[7412] = "";
D.q[4538] = "Actually, you don\'t have to worry about the supply of equipment. Since Nara died, we made the most of our relations with Pandala and got a full convoy of Pandawa equipment. We fooled the Brakmarians by convincing them that our ship, the Panta Maria, was transporting these materials. While they were chasing the Panta Maria, the equipment was sent by land and it arrived last night. Captain Alrok and his men are already examining it.";
D.q[8043] = "";
D.q[7670] = "It is a versatile profession. Alchemists are both collectors and artisans. The potions and elixirs that they produce are very powerful and often related to magic. By collecting specific plants and mixing them with talent, an alchemist is capable of performing miracles.";
D.q[5761] = "";
D.q[3979] = "Okay! Touch my paw and set off.";
D.q[8044] = "";
D.q[1232] = "Well, it\'s not cold enough. It must have warmed up on your way back.\nYou\'re lucky that this is how I like it!";
D.q[7671] = "Dragonsly has a workshop in Astrub. You won\'t find it hard to spot him there. He won\'t just teach his skills to anyone, though.";
D.q[8045] = "";
D.q[6832] = "You again? Your stories about spelling are even less interesting than the ones about owls. Leave me alone, now, a fight\'s about to start.";
D.q[4028] = "The recipe is not complete? But I\'ve told you everything I know...";
D.q[6885] = "What are you talking about? My beloved Hypnomeow wouldn\'t dare mistreat me. He\'s so cute with his little fangs and his bloodshot eyes.";
D.q[817] = "We broke many weapons during the training of the recruits. Many skulls too, but let\'s not worry about that. The new weaponry is in the Tower. There are about 10 boxes, go and get them for me.";
D.q[6935] = "Who told you about that? Was it Grizmine? Kwartzwatch? Setag?\nNot that it matters, I\'m not telling you anything.";
D.q[1307] = "Another new tax? Take this cheque then.";
D.q[8046] = "";
D.q[824] = "Our stock of poison is dry. Could you kill some scurvions and take their poison?\nI need at least 20 pods of it, do you think you can manage that?\nActually let me rephrase that, you MUST bring me at least 20 pods or you\'ll regret it #1!";
D.q[811] = "Well, well an innocent soul in this place...If you want to join our cause, bring me 10 twiggy daggers. I\'ve some recruits to train tomorrow.";
D.q[2514] = "Now that the island is open to all, the worship of the goddess Pandawa is going to spread throughout the World... our goddess will earn a greater share of the divine market... the cherries from her table will topple down on us... and let me tell you, we\'ll have our mouths wide open. \n*He glances at you suspiciously*\nHem! I think the walls have ears around here...";
D.q[7020] = "Top o\'the mornin\' to ya! I\'m Sag Dratsum, descendant of the very first Sag the Enutrof.\nAs you can see there\'s plenty of work to do here, the place is a real building site. You might wonder what an Enutrof is doing among all these Pandawas, I\'ll explain in a moment. Us Enutrofs have centuries of experience in the field of drilling. As drilling is my specialty, they hired me to direct operations.\nWhen I arrived it was a real mess here, but since I took things in hand, it\'s a bit better. Still, be careful not to fall into a hole, you\'ll have rotten away to nothing before anyone comes to help you.";
D.q[4751] = "You made sure they\'d never bother us again? Well done, you\'ve shown me you can think for yourself, even if I\'d have preferred to have had them join my henchmen. On the other hand, a few incompetents more or a few less... what\'s the difference?";
D.q[7077] = "";
D.q[8047] = "";
D.q[4333] = "Now is the time. Take the jewel and find Xephires at the Drunken Pandawa Inn. I don\'t trust you to explain the plan, so I\'m going to write it all down for him.\nOh, and don\'t even think about keeping the jewel for yourself or selling it - I\'ve spies everywhere and if you ever try to betray me, I can tell you you\'ll regret it. But you wouldn\'t do that now, would you?";
D.q[6280] = "You beat the burglars and managed to make sure they\'d never bother us again? Well done, you\'ve shown me you can think for yourself, even if I\'d have preferred to have had them join my henchmen. On the other hand, a few incompetents more or a few less... what\'s the difference?";
D.q[2723] = "Everyone says those paths are twisting and the creatures which haunt them are not what we call friendly. But a Wally Elconom succeeded to draw a map. It could be useful for you to meet him. He\'s often seen round Amakna.";
D.q[8048] = "";
D.q[7413] = "";
D.q[5572] = "Excellent work! \nI\'ll start making the potion right away, just give me a few minutes.\nThere you go. Use this with the Lear Amulet according to the ritual described in Erzal\'s Blessing. Then come back here to see me.";
D.q[8049] = "";
D.q[5687] = "There\'s not a moment to lose. Take several Spamouflage Potions with you and go through the Tofu House with a fine-toothed comb. Brakmar cannot get the statuette before we do.";
D.q[6253] = "That\'ll do for the guard. I\'m going to have the prisoner transferred while you go find a way to contact Captain Starky to tell him that we are holding his niece hostage. If he wants to see her again, he\'ll have to give us Kain Dharyn\'s crystal. Stampitor upstairs knows his rival well, ask him if you want to know anything. When you\'ve delivered the message, go see Sabine to make sure that all is going well... and wait for news from the enemy.";
D.q[6067] = "";
D.q[1570] = "Right now? To defend the ramparts? Grmph I don\'t have any left. But... It might be a good opportunity to test my new creation. It\'s fragile but the range makes up for it...The only drawback is that it\'s too powerful to shoot at anything close by.";
D.q[8050] = "";
D.q[6837] = "There is a breed of very lazy Bow Meow that is able to hypnotize its victims to make them carry out its every whim. Once trained, a bow meow like that would be very useful to us, if we could find one.\nGo see Oshimo, the guardian of the Kennel, and ask him if he has a Hypnomeow in reserve. If he has one but it\'s not yet trained, and when I say that I mean the Hypnomeow, not Oshimo, take it to Riyou Tchevlakouk. This Bow Meow tamer is currently conducting community service next to the Pet Market. He should be able to train the Hypnomeow in less time than it takes to say the Schmilidibili the Scmiill the shemyil the Schimilimi the libimliibili the...";
D.q[4780] = "The militia? Who do you take me for? I had no evidence and they would have dragged me off for defamation, the clowns! What do you think? They look after themselves.";
D.q[7414] = "";
D.q[4863] = "";
D.q[1889] = "Oh, I see, hihihi, your lady sure is lucky. Oh boy, I wish somebody would offer me a little rose as well. A tiny little rose would do. Unfortunately, I\'ve none left, I\'m very sorry. I can\'t go and fetch any right now but I can tell you where you can find some.";
D.q[2524] = "O! Pandawaaa! Hear my prayers: Goddess, a li\'l drink, we\'re thirsty, Goddess, a li\'l drink, we\'re thirsty...! Oh, but I\'m missing the most important thing: a flask of Pandneken! We can\'t drink to Pandawa, huh... I mean, make her a libation without a flask of Pandneken! Go see the peddler at the harbour, he has some! Hurry up! The goddess is losing patience!";
D.q[6925] = "t seems that after several years the Ecaflip was finally unable to keep his mouth shut. They\'re all the same. I suppose you bet a large sum to get information from him. What do you want exactly?";
D.q[4900] = "The Hammer of Light? That\'s funny, someone asked me a few days ago about just such a hammer.\nWhen the Iops exiled the Falistos to the Underworld, they destroyed most of their creations. With Iops not being very keen on hammers, those that were not destroyed were enchanted and given as gifts on special occasions or were simply lost. One of these hammers, the Hammer of Light, was given to the city of Bonta after its sudden reappearance.";
D.q[7415] = "";
D.q[8051] = "";
D.q[6827] = "I\'ve told you everything I know. My parents always tell me it\'s not nice to lie. Judging by your face, you lie a lot.";
D.q[1942] = "Oh jolly good! I can see you have a gift for human relationships, which is a very good thing. I\'m going to create your wand. *Nepra pours the Dizbi essence onto an ordinary wood stem, which suddenly comes to life again, a flower growing on its end looking just like one of those Dizbi flowers*. Here is your wand! Look after it, it will get you out of tight spots. Speaking of tight spots, here is your first mission...";
D.q[8052] = "";
D.q[7751] = "";
D.q[7416] = "";
D.q[7588] = "This house belongs to a friend, but he prefers to remain anonymous for now.\nHe opens the doors of his house during the month of December, and only premium access holders may enter.\nYou\'re already wondering what you\'ll find in there, aren\'t you?\nWell, let me explain.";
D.q[6471] = "Maybe he liked women after all, or else it\'s because yours was very small and he was looking for a real man.";
D.q[6788] = "I\'d like to help but I don\'t remember anything else. I\'m sorry. Is he OK, at least? He must find the time drags, alone in his cell.";
D.q[7752] = "";
D.q[602] = "Oh, how did you know that? Yes, I robbed someone once, but I needed that bread, I had no money left and I was starving. Don\'t tell anybody, please, I could end up in prison you know, oh please!";
D.q[4907] = "";
D.q[3393] = "Yes! Good. Not over yet... nothing\'s over, nothing\'s ever finished. Fight again. And again. The key to your next fight.";
D.q[1349] = "*Stone*\nHem, I\'ve lost, you\'re not that bad... Let\'s play the second round.";
D.q[8053] = "";
D.q[8066] = "";
D.q[5312] = "";
D.q[7417] = "";
D.q[8054] = "";
D.q[6884] = "I do not have any Bow Meows like that in my Kennel. However, rumours speak of mysterious disappearances in the forest Amakna, near the border of the evil forest. Further investigation suggests that the disappearances are concentrated between Uba Tesse\'s Alchemists\' Workshop, Abely Bobeule\'s Carvers\' Workshop, and the Lumberjacks\' Workshop located somewhat further east.\nIf these disappearances are the work of a Hypnomeow, it\'s almost certainly hiding with its victims in a remote place. You\'ll have to search the area with a fine-toothed comb.\nIf it helps, Hypnomeows love comfort and do not like the outdoor life at all, so it\'s very likely it\'s found itself a cosy little nest.";
D.q[287] = "Oh I say! Top hole! What a piece of luck! You truly are a decent chap. Marvellous. Bring me 25 Mint Jellies, if you\'ll, and I shall give you a precious blue stone in exchange. Let\'s shake hands to clinch the deal! Spiffing!";
D.q[8067] = "";
D.q[7080] = "";
D.q[1396] = "Oh you can\'t access the questioning quarters? I see... I can give you a temporary pass... Name? #1? \nOh, right! I remember, Oto talked about you at the last meetings. Good work! Here is a permanent pass as a result!";
D.q[8068] = "";
D.q[8055] = "";
D.q[7084] = "";
D.q[260] = "Oh, thanks a lot! Here you are, a magic scroll I found in the attic when I moved in, I\'m sure you\'ll find a use for it.";
D.q[6512] = "A gaming room? I don\'t know what you ... Oh, it\'s you! I\'m sorry, a thousand apologies, I did not want to lie to you. It\'s just that... I can\'t talk about it to anyone, you understand? Here\'s a key so you can go there even if I\'m not here, the hidden entrance is at the back of the room. It\'s always a pleasure to receive a Brakmarian of your rank in our tavern.";
D.q[8069] = "";
D.q[8056] = "";
D.q[7681] = "Blow your nose there, you\'re dripping on your boots.\nAre you here for the YeCh\'Ti?";
D.q[7419] = "";
D.q[6892] = "I bet you wouldn\'t last more than five minutes, but it seems that fate willed otherwise. Next time luck will be on my side and you\'ll end up as black pudding or pâté for my Bow Meow.";
D.q[7587] = "Hi! If you\'re looking to buy a house, you\'ve come to the right place. Thanks to me, you\'ll have a friend in the estate agent business.\nI know what intrigues you, you\'re wondering who owns this house, that\'s hidden away in Cania.";
D.q[6944] = "I am not yet ready for that, I feel like I am finally accustomed to solitude. Is there another way for me to express my gratitude?";
D.q[6964] = "I can sell you all my sick boars if you want, I\'d be glad to get rid of them. Otherwise I\'ll sell them to you one by one for 1,000 Kamas each. I\'d advise you not to stand too close to them, you\'re likely to catch their fleas, their ticks and a whole host of other parasites.";
D.q[7057] = "I am surprised that you have not yet chosen your path. The different Order Masters will be delighted to welcome you into their ranks, so do not hesitate to seek an interview with them in the Tower of Bonta.";
D.q[8057] = "";
D.q[8070] = "";
D.q[8071] = "";
D.q[8058] = "";
D.q[7002] = "Hi, you\'ll never guess what I saw on Otomai Island. Hehehe, no, I\'m not going to tell you, na na nee na na. If you really want to know what it was, ask Otomai directly.\nI\'m sorry but I have many things to do, Greu Nouille is up to her old tricks again and once again it\'s down to me to sort things out. The damned Feca will be the death of me.";
D.q[2255] = "You\'re the backup?! Well, we\'ll have to make do with that...Here\'s the thing: the Osamodas have lent us Tofus who sniff around to smell if there\'s any gas leaks and they warn us when it becomes too dangerous, see? We call them \'sniffallrats\'.";
D.q[2298] = "Meow!";
D.q[7683] = "Just you wait and see, you\'ll get your face kicked in!";
D.q[3132] = "Here you go! Now you know how to hypnotize a Dragoturkey. All you need to do is buy my famous book on Dragoturkey breeding to learn more about the subject. You\'re a nice fellow, but now I\'m feeling better I no longer need you. Besides, people need my knowledge, so leave me alone.";
D.q[2229] = "Thank youu honeyyy! This snack will go straight to my hips, but it really gets you going! WOOHOO!";
D.q[3913] = "Finding a handsome and noble knight is not an easy thing. I don\'t envy you... good luck.";
D.q[8072] = "";
D.q[3565] = "Me know. Me offer you head!";
D.q[2092] = "Fine, I\'ll meet you here.";
D.q[1057] = "Ah great. Brand new dentures. Mak will be happy.";
D.q[8059] = "";
D.q[7420] = "";
D.q[8060] = "";
D.q[1370] = "Oh, a report on the changes in the regional volcanic activities! I had completely forgotten it. You see I\'ve found near the mines bones of primary diabolical animals, which seem to date from the first Divine War...";
D.q[1316] = "Oh, Amayiro finally sent someone to help me?\nHurry, get me out of here!";
D.q[4318] = "A dodgy-looking Ecaflip, you say? I didn\'t notice. But you should ask the girls instead, I think Ecaline had some trouble with an Ecaflip not so long ago.";
D.q[3123] = "I feel like... all young adventurers... like you, come... to steal... the Dofus from me...that\'s already been stolen... by the way... \nI like you... your spirit seems to be... stable, you\'re calm... like a stunned... Dragoturkey... nice... like a squashed Piwi..., generous... like a cut up Gobball... I\'d like to... entrust you with one of my favourite... items... but you\'ll have to... leave my den... and go to... the village... before the other Koalaks come back...";
D.q[8073] = "";
D.q[3179] = "First of all, I forbid you to laugh at me! I can\'t help it if my parents gave me a pet\'s name! When I was young, I used to spend my days playing with Scaraleaves, tearing their wings off or burning their antennas. We didn\'t have much to play with when I was a child... My parents thought it would be a good idea to call me by this name... \nAlright just say it if you\'re not interested in my life! All you\'re looking for is to enter this cave? Well, just give me the key because I\'d like to go too when I\'m stronger!";
D.q[8061] = "";
D.q[6831] = "Ah, that miscreant, denouncing me like that! Next time I\'ll bet his fur on the dice and believe me, I intend to win, and I\'ll make a scarf with it.\nI talk to some of the Srams sometimes when a bit of business requires some skill and some discretion. And no, I\'m not specifically talking about female Srams, although I sometimes also rent their services for similar reasons.\nIf you don\'t believe me, ask that old Lie Heur. He knows much more about what\'s going off here than he cares to admit.";
D.q[3112] = "Singing: \nIf I had a hammer, I\'d knock nails in, \nIf I had a shovel, I\'d plant potatoes, \nIf I had a peeler, I\'d peel potatoes, \nLalalala";
D.q[3476] = "Break bones, slosh brains, gouge out eyes and kill kill kill Bworks!";
D.q[6990] = "Agaklah bouzou. Honk honk! A rolling Glukoko gathers no moss, but a rolling Moskito gathers some glue.\nShaman Surivitna\'s a bad masseur but a good doctor, it\'s not both of mine that he\'s got, but both of his.\nHe\'s looking for a cure for my amnesia, but his previous treatments have made me worse. I feel like I\'m losing my mind, but as this one isn\'t mine, it\'s not too serious.\nI\'ll have a fried Snapper, please.";
D.q[8074] = "";
D.q[4797] = "A Sram? That is interesting. We must find him at all costs!\nSpeaking of fish, Kook Fech has just prepared some for the militia, I\'ve put some aside for you.";
D.q[6806] = "According to you, Robin Gaywould will reveal some valuable information to us if we can ensure he and his boars are kept safe?\nWell, as the leader of the militia and responsible for the security of this city, I must protect its inhabitants. Go see Red Nefed - he\'s taking a break in the Woodenglass Inn - and tell him he is now assigned to monitor Robin Gaywould\'s paddock. Then, return to Robin Gaywould and use your wits to get him to tell you everything he knows about Kit Dingaround and his alleged treason.";
D.q[8062] = "";
D.q[7679] = "Oh, is that true? You are very kind. Be careful, they are still ferocious.\nKiki will be very happy.";
D.q[1494] = "Oh, I knew you weren\'t as thick as you look. Because they have convergent opinions, those 2 thinking heads want to seize the power. Fortunately, the third one is strong enough to resist them.\nIt\'s not time for action. You must train. Go on Moon Island and fight against its renowned turtles. You\'ll soon make progress. You must kill at least 10 of them before you return...";
D.q[8063] = "";
D.q[7680] = "Thank you very much. Here\'s a little pocket money, you\'ve earned it. I still wonder what those Faded Stunted Rats were doing here. I\'m sure it\'s because of all this mess in the pipes. It attracts the rats... Kiki agrees with me!";
D.q[1323] = "Oh, I\'m sorry. It seems I didn\'t make myself clear. I need 20 peeled spuds, 6 crow legs and 3 eyes. Sorry again.";
D.q[8075] = "";
D.q[8064] = "";
D.q[5626] = "You wouldn\'t have some equipment for me, would you? Even a Piwi thing, anything at all. Unless it\'s blue. I hate blue. Blue is ugly. I want something red... or maybe pink. Even purple will do. Or something better still...";
D.q[3394] = "Yes! Good. Not over yet... nothing\'s over, nothing\'s ever finished. Fight again. And again. The key to your next fight.";
D.q[6986] = "Wyrmwells are extremely rare magical items. It seems that the white dragon Dardondakal the Wise owned several, and they were a key to his profound wisdom.\nThere is a place where Dardondakal liked to rest in the Cania Forest. Unfortunately, since his death, this place is buried away. One of my books reveals how to enter, but you must still find the entrance and gather the information necessary for its opening.\nTo do this you need 10 White Dreggon Shells, 5 White Dreggon Eggs and 1 Dreggon Warrior Skin. You\'ll have to search every corner of the Cania Forest, inspect every bush, lift every rock to find the entrance. However, if you do not possess the things I\'ve mentioned, there\'s no point trying.";
D.q[2184] = "A runaway care stone? Give me that, quickly...*Shani rushes to his workroom and comes back two minutes later. The stone has been set into a metal bezel.*  Once it\'s been extracted from the rock, the stone loses its power very quickly. Only this metal can retain the stone\'s power.";
D.q[8065] = "";
D.q[574] = "Oh, nice mask! You could almost pass for a Kanniball! Teehee... But you wouldn\'t go very far away... It\'s an underling\'s mask. You should be thinking of a promotion, hehehe.";
D.q[5634] = "Do you know what Dofus actually means? I always ask myself. More and more people have been talking about them and I\'ve heard some people say that they have a few, so I figured they must be collectible, kind of like stamps or Gobbowl cards. What do you think? Do you know what Dofus means? I\'m still wondering... especially since so many people are talking about it.";
D.q[1319] = "Amaknean Oyster! Spaghetti Bworkonaise! Raaaaavioliiiii! Fried Crackeroni and cheese!\nHuh, hem... What do you want ?";
D.q[5050] = "Ah, you\'re back. I found out what was happening in Amakna and I think Danathor is going too far. It\'s not wise to carry on business with Amakna that damages relations between the towns, especially considering all the trouble that\'s been going on. When you go back to Amakna, try to calm things down with Sergeant Graccia";
D.q[6981] = "For a Xelor, Xeloro Verpowered wasn\'t very good at divination. Nevertheless, I remember she once told me about a rare and powerful magic object, able to preserve and restore thoughts and memories. It was called a Wyrmwell. I would gladly have helped more, but I am no expert on dragons. You would be better off contacting the Master of the Osamodas class, he has a reputation for knowing about dragons, like many other followers of the that god.";
D.q[5448] = "Normally, you\'d have to cross the swamps. I do, however, happen to know a way of getting to the sanctuary without having to come face to face with those horrible crocodyls.\nBefore I tell you anymore, I have something to ask of you. I\'ve learned that Altaïr is giving away Bow Meows to any adventurer who shows up at Gobball Dungeon and introduces himself. Unfortunately, a number of these people don\'t care for them and leave them to starve to death, or worse, abandon them in a bin in Astrub.\nIf you save a Bow Meow and bring it here, I\'ll tell you my secret.";
D.q[7627] = "Could you speak a little quieter, please? So you\'re looking for information about this piece of parchment. It looks as though it comes from a very ancient work: \"Goultard, a hero is born\" by H. Mambillin. Unfortunately, we don\'t have that book in our humble library.";
D.q[1979] = "Gcan I do zobezing for you? *sniff*";
D.q[4986] = "";
D.q[6735] = "Get out of here before I replace the Tofoone with something a little more unpleasant, you idiot.";
D.q[3677] = "Get going! That sort of laziness might get you through Incarnam, but you won\'t get far anywhere else... and you think you\'re gonna find a Dofus. Ha!";
D.q[2292] = "Get outta my way, I\'m busy... ";
D.q[7628] = "I told you, we don\'t have it here! It just so happens that that very work was taken a very long time ago by a great master from a temple in the town. But it was a very long time ago, as I say, and I don\'t remember which master it was. You\'ll be lucky if he\'s still got the Grimoire in his possession after all this time. Knowing a little bit about Goultard might help you avoid having to ask every single temple master or even search every temple. Think carefully about what Goultard was. I wish you luck.";
D.q[2886] = "Alright, then, close your eyes and don\'t open them until I tell you so. Don\'t pay attention to any screams you might hear.";
D.q[7632] = "They tell me you\'re interested in finding out about Goultard\'s past. I\'d be happy to give you the book you\'re looking for but you\'ll have to work for me in return.";
D.q[4182] = "Gniiiii. Gniiii. Vrüt vrüt gniii!";
D.q[5009] = "";
D.q[4795] = "Not exactly. It\'s harder to make him talk than it is to keep a Sadida awake. I have an idea that might work but I need your help.";
D.q[3009] = "Go and see Bolzano Vieilletrasse in the forest of Amakna. If you give him a hand, he\'ll get you one.";
D.q[7633] = "Good, a refusal would have been inappropriate. This book tells us more about Goultard and his childhood. An ambitious plan hatched from my genius brain, and thanks to what I learnt, I am in a position to be able to manipulate Goultard and force him to work for us. Obviously, despite my immense powers, I cannot do this alone. Especially as I suspect the Bontarians are monitoring my every movement. This is where you come in. Meet me at the Tower of Gisgoul, and I\'ll tell you more.";
D.q[3010] = "Go and see Rish Claymore, in the Iop Temple. He\'s a proud warrior and probably has some.";
D.q[7086] = "";
D.q[2570] = "Go to the halbol, then you can boald. Ol you can decide to walk but it\'s longel and mole tiling...";
D.q[3481] = "Gob cavalry help me, you die and me sell your skin to Bworks!!!";
D.q[1031] = "Ohoh, I see you\'re quick to obey. You could be useful to the infernal clan. I\'ve made up my mind, from now on, you\'ll take your orders from me. If things don\'t work out, at least you can replace one of the chafers.";
D.q[7635] = "There you are at last! Listen carefully to the first step of my plan. I need you to find the Gisgouls\' Vault and bring back the items that belonged to them. I\'ll bewitch them to...I\'ll reveal everything when you get back. The vault is somewhere in the Cemetery of the Tortured. Go, and hurry!";
D.q[7672] = "I hope you didn\'t lose it, at least. No? So much the better, Amayiro would have been most unhappy.";
D.q[5598] = "Ok, here\'s what we\'re going to do - you\'re going to go to Merlinmagus\'s place and replace his Poppy Seeds with Scurvion Seeds. Wait for nightfall to make your way, for if you\'re seen our plan will come to nothing.";
D.q[7638] = "Perfect, that will do. Now, go and get me all the things I need for the ritual while I prepare the area where the enchantment will take place. Some Vampire Blood to restore the soul of the dead to life, some Oni Blood to corrupt their vision, and finally some Scurvion Blood, a poison for the mind. If you\'re quick I\'ll be sure to remember what you\'ve done for me.";
D.q[3477] = "Goblin no want be a tapestry in Workshop.";
D.q[7087] = "";
D.q[1052] = "God\'dam\'! But yar som good\'boy, aient ya? Com\' here body, letz talk about thingz to celebrate this round\'!";
D.q[3655] = "Hello, can I help you?";
D.q[7644] = "Well, well, well, what\'s that I see? A Bwork ready to serve my mistress? Excellent, he\'ll make me a few Kamas, that\'s for sure. He\'ll cause a riot in the Arenas of Time. I haven\'t been twiddling my thumbs either, the trap is set, it\'s just waiting for its prey.";
D.q[7645] = "Your involvement is almost at an end. We must now help Dark Vlad escape from his labyrinth. Go put down some maps in the Evil Forest, without getting killed, if possible - as well as some intelligence potions, he\'s not the sharpest tool in the box when he\'s in Dark Vlad mode, this Goultard... well, so much the better to catch him when it he\'s not at his best.";
D.q[1296] = "WHAT! The Oto is such a swindler! Take this then. Anyway I shouldn\'t complain after all... with the number of officers who wind up here...";
D.q[5581] = "Ok, I\'ll think about your offer. It doesn\'t matter to me how exactly you got this money, but as long as you pay up, we can do business.\nI\'m actually going to tell you how to convince me, that\'s how nice I am. I can\'t manage to sell my goods in Astrub because Mawy Ingalsse is flooding the market with cheap cereals. Not only that, but his product has a very good reputation due to the way in which he cultivates his crops. I can\'t go near his workshop without arousing suspicion, so I want you to go there and convince Emia Elliesol to sabotage his work. I don\'t care how you do it, just do it.";
D.q[3712] = "Piwi piwi";
D.q[3965] = "Okay, that\'s enough for the moment. I\'ll recruit some swordsmen. Come and see me later.";
D.q[1505] = "Ok, grab the rope. Well done. How is your long-range attack? Because you\'ll need it now.";
D.q[7646] = "You\'ve served me well, but all this must remain our little secret, you understand. Rushu does not want any rumours about the impending conversion of Goultard to his cause to be heard on the streets of Brakmar. I\'ll leave you in the capable hands, well, claws of my creatures.";
D.q[3920] = "Good morning, faithful servant! Long live our beloved King! May he... Huh, what? If something special is happening at the castle? Why are you asking this? Get lost!";
D.q[4129] = "Congratulations! You managed to repel the pirates. I told you it would be an eventful journey... \nFortunately, we\'re almost there, if I\'m reading the map correctly.";
D.q[7650] = "You seem to be paying close attention to the history of Goultard. And you\'re not alone. The Brakmarian scum are active in the abandoned village of Gisgoul. Why are they there? Quite simply, that\'s where Goultard spent his childhood. Our spies have not returned. Apparently they were captured by Bworks and taken to their village. Head over there and liberate our scout-spy.";
D.q[4040] = "Good! You\'ve got the dress! The wedding should start!";
D.q[7655] = "Free! I\'m free! Thank you, I really thought I was going to end up in the pot that time. Lets get out of here and I\'ll tell you everything I know. I know that I can trust you and I owe you that much.";
D.q[6286] = "Good, you\'ve won. I\'ll deliver the letter to Xephires, but please leave me alone.";
D.q[1537] = "Good! Anyway, we\'ve decided to change our assault plans. That way it makes a double surprise.";
D.q[1134] = "Oh, aren\'t these hammers pretty! Do they have them in black?";
D.q[7656] = "Well, now that I\'m safe, here is all the information I have obtained on Gisgoul and the activities of the Brakmarians. They plan to use Goultard and enslave the world. Nothing new there but they seem to have a plan. I\'ve heard mention of the Cemetery of the Tortured and the grave of Goultard\'s mother. But I was caught before I could make my way there. The Bworks are not working for them, that\'s something at least. I think Lethaline Sigisbul is behind it.";
D.q[6302] = "I\'m surprised that someone of your rank even knows such a place exists. I know where it is, but I don\'t want to share my hard-won information free of charge... we are in Brakmar after all, aren\'t we. Bring me the soul of a Vampire Master so I can make some Nightmarish Incense and I\'ll not only tell you where the place is, but I\'ll even give you a few tips on getting in.";
D.q[2849] = "Good. And if you have a Kannipiwi cap or a Guava cap, which one will bring you most experience in fight?";
D.q[1085] = "Good. But I\'m sure there are some missing. Try again!";
D.q[2699] = "Grandapan knows a lot of things! The Dofus receptacle is a genuine relic passed down by our ancestors... but don\'t tell me that\'s all you\'ve seen. Doesn\'t it prove the truth of the legend? Go ahead and have a look, and decide for yourself whether it\'s true or not.";
D.q[7658] = "You have done well, but there one thing left to do. According to Bonta\'s sages, the cursed item\'s purpose was to attract Dark Vlad to the grave of his mother. Brakmarian forces are placing maps in the maze to guide Dark Vlad. They should by no means succeed. You must stop them. Find and destroy the hints scattered by the Brakmarians.";
D.q[1211] = "You seem to be hesitating between ease and decay of good and the glory of evil. \nIf it\'s you\'re finding it hard to make a decision, go and see Oto Mutsam, he\'ll help you out.";
D.q[7659] = "You\'re doing your utmost to thwart my diabolical schemes. Do you think I know nothing? I\'ll show you what happens when you make me angry. DIE!";
D.q[1231] = "I wasn\'t working last night. The only one here was that drunkard over there...";
D.q[3395] = "Yes! Good. Not over yet... nothing\'s over, nothing\'s ever finished. Fight again. And again. The key to your next fight.";
D.q[7660] = "That\'s fantastic, you were able to stop the Brakmarians carrying out their dark plan. I\'m so happy I could cry. As a reward for this heroic act, I\'d like to give you an item that belonged to Goultard when he was a child. Which one would you like?";
D.q[7666] = "I understand, forgive my distrust. This gem contains a dark power that must be broken. I will seek advice from Iop. He will know what to do. Your task is complete and you should celebrate because without your intervention, who knows what evil this object would have caused. You\'ve incriminated Lethaline and justice must be served. Post these notices in the villages and towns so that all bounty hunters are aware that a reward is offered for her capture.";
D.q[7682] = "Ahem!\n\"\n- Team must be made up of a maximum of four people.\n- It is FORBIDDEN to have several characters of the same class in the same team. Any team with at two or more characters of the same class will be automatically disqualified.\n- Once the fight starts, each team has 30 minutes maximum in which to defeat the YeCh\'Ti.\n- If the battle is lost before the 30 minutes are up, or if the battle is still ongoing after 30 minutes, the team is considered as having lost. \"";
D.q[1346] = "*Waves his hand*";
D.q[745] = "Won\'t you give me a break? No sooner have I given you a job to do than you\'re back here looking for more.\nFor the moment I\'ve nothing for you. But I received a letter for you.";
D.q[7693] = "I was already struggling to provide bread for the whole village before, so now with the influx of mainlanders, it\'s even worse. But we have to see the good side of things, the more adventurers there are, the more people there will be to settle the score with the Count.";
D.q[2678] = "Great! Now you\'re one of US! May bamboo bloom under your feet, and ferment in the breeze of your gassy breath! Go see the Shaman Surivitna, he will teach you everything you need to know, as a Pandawa.";
D.q[7707] = "Because you think we have time? The animals won\'t be twiddling their thumbs waiting for you to make a decision, unless ... you\'re working for them, right?";
D.q[3555] = "Green skin good wallpaper.";
D.q[7288] = "";
D.q[6455] = "A dodgy, drunken Ecaflip that you can smell from about 20 leagues away? I know of a few, but there\'s been one that\'s really been bothering one of my waitresses lately. She\'s young... and it still bothers her. If you touch a bloody hair on her head, I\'ll call the guards on you. Got it!?";
D.q[715] = "I\'ve another mission for you, more interesting than the last one.\nMy friend Ned is a dental fanatic and for his latest dentures, he just needs some replacement teeth to make a full set.\nI think you can easily deal with that matter, can\'t you?";
D.q[2093] = "There\'s no two ways about it... this mission is very important!";
D.q[7695] = "I loved how you put those Mastogobs in their place. Hopefully it will calm their ardour for a while and we will be able to resume work soon.";
D.q[7708] = "Ahahah, just kidding! You\'re too puny, you\'d only make a snack for the creatures outside the city, and I don\'t want to have to go and see the mayor and tell her that another tourist is dead because of me.";
D.q[723] = "The innkeeper of the Kikim has unpaid debts to me. I\'d like you to go get my money back. Don\'t hesitate to resort to force if needed \'cause that rogue always has a good excuse to avoid the payment.\nThese 100,000 Kamas should make it possible to repair the blade of my katana. It costs a fortune...";
D.q[2560] = "I can see by youl bloodshot eye that you callied out youl mission! You deselve to know the stoly of oul people.";
D.q[7722] = "Hello dear tourist, allow me to introduce myself. I am the disciple of Sram Fred Handed. Ah, that belongs to you? I\'m so sorry, it looks so much like mine it\'s an easy mistake to make.                                     What? You want me to put these jewels back where I found them? Of course, I was only looking at them.\nIf I could give you some advice, never trust an honest man. Why? Well, quite simply, you never know when they\'re going to betray you. It\'s exactly the opposite with the rest of us, the disciples of Sram.\nOh, is that your Purse of Kamas I\'m holding? You must have mislaid it, you\'re lucky I found it.";
D.q[5933] = "Greetings, How did the meeting with Maimane go?";
D.q[7544] = "Greetings wimp! Wanna get in my arena, that\'s it? Choose your answer well!";
D.q[1213] = "Greetings #1! I didn\'t see you come in... But I can see you\'ve improved your strength since our last meeting!\nWhat can I do for you?";
D.q[166] = "You don\'t have a deck of Tragic the Gardening cards, so you can\'t play that game with me.\nCome back when you have found one...";
D.q[7696] = "It would be best to start my quest where I left off. Find Cabotine\'s tomb in the Cemetery of the Tortured. Good luck.";
D.q[7743] = "Hello, and welcome to the FailHax Estate Agency.\nIf you\'re looking for the house of your dreams or a paddock in which to raise your Dragoturkeys, you\'ve come to the right place.\nOur agents keep a permanent list of all houses and paddocks for sale, to give you the best choice at low, low prices.\nDon\'t hesitate to check out our offers as often as you like.";
D.q[7746] = "The system of greenhouses heated by steam that you see behind me allows us to grow new plants and cereals. Although it might not have won any prizes for agricultural invention, it is now our best chance of fighting against famine.\nMost of the cereals from intensive agriculture weren\'t able to resist the freeze, but thanks to breeding different strains, we have recently developed a new species of hardy cereal: Frosteez. Thanks to this plant we should survive, but it is not ready yet.";
D.q[1516] = "The problem, impatient youth, has its roots in the emergence of Djaul\'s worshippers. More and more Brakmarians worship this demon without honour. People no longer believe in a blow for blow. They want everything to perish, not only Bonta. The dark balance is in danger. Djaul\'s worship threatens the general peace. All Brakmarians have a passion for darkness but now, they\'re divided by the way they venerate it.";
D.q[1696] = "Sorry, you don\'t have enough Trool Tokens.";
D.q[1517] = "I just want you to think about it. Which cult do you follow? Do you support the destruction of Bonta. Will you help us make good our revenge? Or do you want absolute power and the death of every living thing? Are you an honourable soul? Or are you just like Oto who will ignore all morals to achieve his goals? Your choice is very important. Take this ring. When you have made your decision, come back to me. Give me back the ring if you wish to belong to Djaul\'s movement.";
D.q[1475] = "Creatures that are gobbling our walls?! Pretty dangerous... I hope they haven\'t made holes in our defences...We need to check that right now: take Mac with you, go through the deepest sewer and make sure there\'s no exit!";
D.q[1190] = "The Orders are armed groups, in charge of upholding honour and equality in our world.\nThe three great Orders of Bonta are the Sharp Eye, the Salvatory Spirit and the Valiant Heart.\nOf course, each of them has its customs, its proper methods to see its tasks through to the end.\nIt would take me hours to describe you all the subtleties of those three Orders.";
D.q[7754] = "This will come in handy for starting new research alongside the experiments to improve our cereals. If we manage to diversify products made from Frigostian cereals, we will be in a position to overtake Amakna. Then finally we can get rid of Count Harebourg.";
D.q[5019] = "";
D.q[6047] = "Greetings, what good news do you have for me today? You always bring me good news, don\'t you.";
D.q[7788] = "I\'ll take a look at that wight now.\n...\n............................\nThat\'s incwedible! The specimens you\'ve bwought me look like the ones I found sevewal yeaws ago on Wabbit Island. Might it be the same species that has evolved and adapted to the climate? If that\'s the case, that could explain why the wabbits awe so agwessive.\nI need Otomai\'s help to analyse the pathogen the ticks pass on to theiw host. Take him this envelope, it contains my conclusions and hypotheses. Bwing me back his answew.";
D.q[7789] = "Is that for me?\nInteresting, very interesting. A nice example of evolution and adaptation to a hostile environment.\nGo tell the Wogew the Hewmit that I will study it more closely and will keep him abreast of the progress of my research.";
D.q[7807] = "Several of my lads went to get wood but they never returned. I fear they have been attacked by forest creatures, or worse.\nYou look pretty handy, what would you say to going and finding out what happened to them? I\'ll show you where I sent them.";
D.q[2010] = "Aaaah! Bring me a Gobball back to replace the one you\'ve just killed!";
D.q[7810] = "Richard accuses me of being too hot-headed and treats me like a kid. He thinks I don\'t have a clue about his plan to ingratiate himself with my sister. Meanwhile, Mr. Knowitall has still not found a solution to get us out of here.";
D.q[2245] = "Grmbl... I\'m sick of these bloody creatures! They gobble up all my fruits! Could you help me get rid of them?";
D.q[7811] = "We\'ve been going round in circles for days. I\'m sure you would have panicked if you\'d have been in this situation, but not us. Red will find a way out of here for us, it\'s just a matter of time.\nWhat worries me most are the creatures that are lurking around here. If I don\'t stay alert, I\'m afraid they\'ll do for my friends.";
